# API GUIDELINES

Source: [`docs/CONSTITUTION.md`](docs/CONSTITUTION.md) IV, [`docs/TECHNICAL.md`](docs/TECHNICAL.md) §7. Consult `core.mdc`, `backend.mdc`.

**OpenAPI workflow:** `openapi-contract-sync` skill (export/codegen commands not in TECHNICAL).

## Scope

`Solution.Api` — thin HTTP. **MediatR only** in handlers; map to `Solution.Contracts` DTOs — never serialize domain entities.

## REST surface (sample)

| Area | Method / path | Handler |
|------|---------------|---------|
| Auth | `POST /api/users` | RegisterUser |
| Auth | `POST /api/auth/login` | LoginUser |
| Auth | `POST /api/auth/logout` | LogoutUser |
| Auth | `GET /api/auth/me` | GetCurrentUser |
| Health | `GET /health` | Aspire defaults |

## Success response

Return the resource DTO directly (no custom `{ data, meta }` envelope).

## Errors — RFC 7807

- `code` — stable machine identifier
- Validation failures → field extensions in `errors`

## Status mapping

| Status | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `200` | Read success |
| `201` | Created (user registered) |
| `204` | Logout / no body |
| `400` | Malformed JSON / binding failure |
| `401` | No session |
| `404` | Resource not found |
| `422` | Domain / validation rejection |
| `500` | Unhandled — generic client message |

## Auth

- Cookie session; Redis cache, PG `user_sessions` authoritative
- Public: register + login only
- Ownership enforced in **Application** handlers (Constitution II.7)

## DON'TS

- ❌ No `200` with error body — use correct status
- ❌ No domain types in OpenAPI/JSON responses
